v5.0 05/13/2018
-rewrote the entire build_single_site() & build_multi_site(). Spawned multiple supporting functions and added support to tput
-running in debug mode disables most tputs commands
-Cleaned up image listing routines
-added CLI switch to control pause timeout after container build. Will help speedup execution on faster systems
-Incorporated last_ip_used fix reported by user csiess. Thank you
-Set --dns switch (at docker run) to 127.0.0.1 if network is missing
-Rearranged startup screen. Lines are now accurately centered (internal row,col caluction bug)
-Added pause timer to header status bar
-Added FreeDisk space to footer status bar
-Rearranged splunk menu selection letters and made them consistant with image screens
-added delete all container cli switch (-d). User has the ability to delete all containers upon script start
-added timer switch (-t). User has the ability to adjust pause timer upon script start. Faster systems can handle smaller pause timer. User should experiment with ideal value.

v5.0.1 05/14/2018 (Splunk 7.1.0 changes):
-support for all missing splunk images up to 7.1.0 (new entrypoint.sh to accomidate new pass requirements)
-Changed default splunk password from "hello" to "hello1234" to accomidate 7.1.0+ releases pass requirements
-fixed few spots where $USERPASS (hello1234) is hard coded
-Set allowRemoteLogin=always in /opt/splunk/etc/system/default/server.conf





